# Jira — bestie.mx work

For **all bestie.mx–related** planning, backlog, epics, stories, and tasks:

- **Jira site:** `https://enbaos.atlassian.net`
- **Project:** **BES** (board: `https://enbaos.atlassian.net/jira/software/projects/BES`)
- **Project settings (access, etc.):** `https://enbaos.atlassian.net/jira/software/projects/BES/settings/access`

When creating or updating Jira issues via MCP, use **`user-Atlassian-MCP-Server`** with cloud id **`2aeff5e5-4ae4-4f40-94f1-6299199597e1`** (hostname **`enbaos.atlassian.net`**) and project key **`BES`** unless the user specifies otherwise.

Prefer linking work to **BES** instead of other Jira projects for this codebase.

## When to set status to **Done** (critical)

- **Do not** move issues to **Done** for backlog import, planning-only work, or “ticket created” milestones.
- **Only** transition to **Done** after the issue’s scope is **implemented in this repo**, **committed**, and **pushed (merged) to the canonical GitHub branch** (typically `main` on `enbatose/bestie.mx`), unless the user explicitly defines a different completion gate.
- For parent epics: leave **To Do** / **In Progress** until **all** agreed child work is merged (or split the epic).
- If unsure, leave the issue **To Do** or **In Progress** and add a **comment** with progress instead of closing.
